SUMMARY:2026 Winter First-Year Engineering Exam Jam
DESCRIPTION:U of T Engineering’s Exam Jam for the 2026 Winter Term will be held in person on Wednesday\, April 8\, 2026 from 10 a.m.–4 p.m. No registration is required\, and all events are free of charge for first-year engineering students. \nWe hope you’ll take advantage of some of these de-stressing and extra help opportunities: \n\nReview sessions with your first-year course instructors and/or TAs;\nHealthy free snacks and de-stressing activities for first-year students from 1 – 3 p.m.;\nTherapy Dog Visit from the Sunshine Therapy Dogs of Toronto from 1 – 2 p.m.\n\nExam Jam Schedule\n\n\n\nTime\nEvent\nLocation\nDescription\n\n\n\n\n10–11 a.m.\nAPS105\nMC 102\nReview session\n\n\n10–11 a.m.\nMIN120\nMC 254\nReview session\n\n\n11 a.m.–12 p.m.\nMIE100\nMC 102\nReview session\n\n\n11 a.m.–12 p.m.\nCIV100\nMC 254\nReview session\n\n\n12–1 p.m.\nCHE112\nMC 102\nReview session\n\n\n12–1 p.m.\nMSE120\nMC 254\nReview session\n\n\n1–2 p.m.\nFree snacks\nMC Lobby\nGrab some free healthy snacks (while supplies last!) in the MC Lobby with the FYO team\n\n\n1–2 p.m.\nTherapy Dog Visit\nGB 202\nDe-stress with furry friends from the Sunshine Therapy Dog program!\n\n\n1–3 p.m.\nGEARS Drop-in Study Sessions\nSF 2402 (Engineering Library Classroom)\nJoin GEARS student mentors to study\, review\, and share exam prep tips!\n\n\n1–3 p.m.\nRelaxing Crafts & Activities\nSF 2402 (Engineering Library)\nDrop by for free and fun activities in the Library! Featuring games\, puzzles\, cute spring crafts\, origami and colouring! Snacks will also be available.\n\n\n2–3 p.m.\nMAT187\nMC 102\nReview session\n\n\n3–4 p.m.\nAPS106\nMC 102\nReview session
URL:https://www.engineering.utoronto.ca/event/2026-winter-first-year-engineering-exam-jam/
LOCATION:Multiple Locations
CATEGORIES:2026 Winter Term,Info sessions,Socials
ORGANIZER;CN="First Year Office":MAILTO:firstyear@engineering.utoronto.ca
END:VEVENT
